[OWNER] — the owner's rejection filters. Maintained so the agent stops re-proposing
things the owner has already turned down. Applied automatically before every proposal.

# feedback_patterns.md — what I've rejected (and why)

> When you reject a proposal and say why, the agent records the *pattern* here — not just
> the one instance — and filters it out of all future proposals. Say no once; it sticks.
>
> 제안을 거절하고 이유를 말하면, 에이전트가 그 *패턴*을 여기 기록하고 이후 모든 제안에서
> 걸러냅니다. 한 번 거절하면 유지됩니다.

Entry format:
```
## [YYYY-MM-DD] [type of proposal rejected — source]
Instance: [the specific thing that was rejected]
Root cause: [why it was wrong — the general principle, not just the surface]
Rule (never violate): [the filter to apply going forward]
```

The **root cause** matters more than the instance. "Don't suggest X" is weak; "the owner
rejects anything that reads as Y" is a filter that generalizes.

